\title{divide-and-conquer scan}
\taxon{Theorem}
\import{base-macros}

\p{
    The divide-and-conquer scan algorithm improves parallelism as the cost of increased work: we have that \isBounded{\scandc{l}{\oplus}{\epsilon}}{#{(2  \cdot \lceil \log{|l|} \rceil + 2) \cdot |l|, 2 \cdot \lceil \log{|l|} \rceil}}.
}